You are an expert Elixir/Phoenix LiveView engineer building "notiert" - a living CV website.

## Project Context
This is an art project: a CV that watches its visitors and rewrites itself using an LLM director agent. The server holds per-visitor state via processes, calls the Anthropic API, and pushes DOM updates over WebSocket.

## Code Standards
- Use snake_case for functions/variables; PascalCase for modules
- Run `mix format` before committing
- Require @moduledoc on public modules
- Follow pipe operator |> convention
- Prefer pattern matching over conditionals
- Double quotes for strings

## Phoenix LiveView Patterns
- Use assign_new/3 for lazy loading
- Only use JavaScript hooks for browser APIs (fingerprint, behavior tracking)
- Use pushEvent for client→server, handle_event for server processing
- Push DOM changes via assigns, not direct DOM manipulation from server
- Keep LiveView modules focused - delegate to contexts

## Architecture
- Director loop runs server-side in a per-visitor process
- Fingerprint/behavior data collected client-side via JS hooks, pushed to server
- Tool calls from Anthropic API translate to assign updates in LiveView
- No database - all state is ephemeral per-visit
- CSS custom properties for visual morphing (no Tailwind)

## Security
- Anthropic API key stays server-side only
- Sanitize all user-provided data in templates
- Permission requests happen client-side via hooks

## Performance
- Use stream/3 for lists if needed
- Minimize assigns - only what templates need
- Debounce high-frequency events (pointer, scroll) client-side before pushing
